SUMMARY:Hope Café at I-House
DESCRIPTION:I-House in Davis has invited artist Jesikah Maria Ross to dream up another interactive\, art-filled gathering that brings folks together to play\, share stories and lift each other up. It’s called Hope Café.  She piloted the event last year\, and we think our community could use another one right about now. \nAt Hope Café you’ll get some time away from the news cycle and instead experience: \n\nLocal artists jazzing up the space with music and poetry\nLighthearted activities that spark curiosity and delight\nConversations that build connection in creative\, human ways\n\nMay’s Hope Café features world jazz duo Nick Carvajal and Jim Frink\, as well as the youth acapella quartet Davis Local Vocals—Evie Barnett\, Ruby Schwerin\, Charlotte DelFavero\, and Matthew Vallero. \nAll of it unfolds in a warm\, welcoming space – complete with snacks! You’ll leave feeling recharged and inspired. \n 
